column26:
Yes, critical illnesses are covered by SmartMedicare. However, there are several conditions to consider:

* **Pre-existing Conditions**: SmartMedicare provides benefits for existing illnesses, subject to certain limits depending on the plan selected, and with a waiting period. You must declare to AXA Indonesia any illness you suffered from before joining AXA Indonesia (listed in the application form) [2831a229-ea3f-491b-b1d8-8a435aa5bcb5, 12:15, "Yes, SmartMedicare provides benefits for pre-existing conditions (those that have been suffered previously) with certain limits according to the chosen plan, with a waiting period. For example, plans A, B and C, pre-existing conditions will be guaranteed after 9 (nine) consecutive months from the start of the policy period. This is provided as long as you declare to AXA any illness you suffered from before you joined AXA (listed in the SPPA/Application Form)."].
* **Specified Diseases**: All specified diseases are excluded during the first twelve (12) months from the effective date of the Policy [5396244b-d87c-45e8-9f49-ddc116182e93, 400:403, "6.2 All specified diseases during the first twelve (12) months from the effective date of the Policy."]. Examples of specific illnesses include stones in the urinary tract system, heart and blood vessel diseases, cataracts, all types of cancer/tumors/cysts, diabetes mellitus, etc. [5396244b-d87c-45e8-9f49-ddc116182e93, 638:679, "4.20 Specific Illnesses
shall mean the following medical conditions occurring within the first twelve (12) months of the commencement / effective date of this Policy, irrespective of whether the Insured Person was aware of the medical condition or not:
4.20.1 Stones in the Urinary system, chronic renal failure; stones or infection of the Biliary system;
4.20.2 Hypertension, Cardio-vascular Disease, Cerebro-Vascular Disease
4.20.3 Cataracts;
4.20.4 All cancers / tumors / polyps / cysts / nodules of any kind including breast lumps;
4.20.5 Nasal or sinus conditions requiring surgery, Abnormalities of the Nasal Septum or Turbinates;
4.20.6 Tonsillitis
4.20.7 Hernias, Hemorrhoids, Fistulae;
4.20.8 Diabetes mellitus, Hyperthyroidism, Hypothyroidism;
4.20.9 Hepatitis
4.20.10 Gastritis, duodenitis, Gastric or Duodenal Ulcer;
4.20.11 Endometriosis, including diseases of the reproductive system, and Adenomyosis;
4.20.12 Rheumatic/Gout, Musculoskeletal disorders;
4.20.13 Tuberculosis, Asthma."].
* **Stent Installation or Bypass Surgery**: Stent installation or bypass surgery is included in the policy coverage if it is not an existing disease. If it is considered an existing condition and was declared at the time of initial policy closing, the benefit limit for this procedure is included in the existing condition benefit limit and there is a waiting period, depending on the selected plan. [2831a229-ea3f-491b-b1d8-8a435aa5bcb5, 9:12, "Stenting or bypass surgery is covered by the policy if it is not a pre-existing condition. If it is considered a pre-existing condition and was declared at the time of initial policy closing, the benefit limit for this procedure is included in the pre-existing condition benefit limit and there is a waiting period, depending on the selected plan."].

